headline: 5 Insightful Analyst Questions From Raymond James’s Q4 Earnings Call
summary: Raymond James delivered fourth-quarter results that saw sales rise year-on-year, though revenue slightly missed Wall Street’s expectations. Management pointed to robust adviser recruiting and retention as significant contributors to the quarter’s growth, with net new asset inflows reaching one of the highest levels in company history.
